LOCATIONS

Nationstar Mortgage is headquartered in Dallas, TX, with major outposts in Irvine, CA; Chandler, AZ; Highlands Ranch, CO; and Chennai, India. We have a total of ninety offices all over the USA, all of which are always on the lookout for talented professionals to join the Nationstar team. Click here to see a full list of current openings in all locations or view by our main locations below. 



















Dallas, TX 









Irvine, CA 









Highlands Ranch, CO 










Chandler, AZ 









Chennai, India 









DALLAS, TX

Twenty-three of the 100 richest Americans live here. German chocolate cake was invented here. We can’t confirm the rumor that the cowboy hat was invented in Munich. Dallas has the biggest arts district in the country. The microchip was invented here. So was the ATM, which came in handy for the guy who invented the microchip. 
View All Jobs in Dallas





CHANDLER, AZ

It’s probably the only town in the world named after a Canadian veterinarian. Folley Street is named after the late Zora Folley, a former city councilman and ex- heavyweight contender who once fought Muhammad Ali. Notable past and current residents of Chandler include pro wrestler Shawn Michaels, rapper Ice-T, and legendary NFL player (and Coca-Cola ad star) “Mean Joe” Greene. It was named the 12th best place to run in and the 10th best place to fitness walk in the US. It is a little odd that the walkers finished ahead of the runners.
View All Jobs in Chandler



CHENNAI, INDIA

Chennai is home to Asia’s largest library, the Anna Centenary Library. It has a capacity of 1.2 million books and is built on eight acres of land. Until 1996, Chennai’s official name was Madras. Its bustling modern auto industry has earned it the nickname “The Detroit of South Asia”. Chennai is a beach destination. Its Marina Beach is 3.7 miles long, making it the world’s second-longest urban beach.
View All Jobs in Chennai



IRVINE, CA

LA Fitness and In-N-Out Burger are both headquartered here, making it easy to work off that Double Double and “Animal Style” fries. Irvine is seventh in the nation when it comes to people over twenty-five years old who hold doctorates.   Never, ever get into a Trivial Pursuit game for money if you’re here. It was named as one of the ten best cities to raise kids. Rage Against the Machine frontman Zack de la Rocha, actor Will Ferrell, and Olympic swimmer Amanda Beard were all raised here. (Hmm, there might be something to that great place to raise kids ranking).
View All Jobs in Irvine



HIGHLANDS RANCH, CO

It was once claimed for France as part of Louisiana. Le Oops. It has over seventy miles of trails. Eighty-five percent of all homes here are within a quarter mile of a park. Highlands Ranch has four dog parks. We’re not sure what percentage of dogs lives within a quarter mile of a dog park. They didn’t respond to our email.
View All Jobs in Highlands Ranch









