Long History of Providing Solutions to Our Customers
   Our Commitment At Nationstar, we believe in keeping the dream of homeownership alive, and we’re on a mission to make the home loan journey more rewarding and less worrisome for our customers. How We’re Helping Homeowners  Over the last year, we helped more than 65,000 customers stay in their homes through modifications and HARP refinances.1 When a payment solution is needed, it’s our goal to find the best option for each customer. Over the last year, we helped customers save an average of $3,550 annually through loan modifications.1 We partner with government and non-profit organizations to find the right solutions to keep our customers in their homes. We’ve participated in 50 community events nationwide meeting face-to-face with more than 700 customers who need help.1   We’re Focused on Preventing Foreclosures  Our goal is to help our customers stay in their homes, and we do everything we can to prevent foreclosures. It’s better for the customer and our business to find ways to modify troubled loans and prevent foreclosures. Keeping customers current on their payments is a win-win for everyone. Over the last year, we helped 39,000 customers transition from delinquent to current on their home loan.1 We aim to be a helpful resource when our customers need us most, so we partner with HUD certified housing counseling agencies to assist with foreclosure prevention, credit repair, budget counseling and pre-purchase counseling.  Customer Service Is In Our DNA  We know that a great customer experience is built by doing a million little things right, so we’re building on our track record of customer service knowing even small improvements can lead to big impacts. We redefined our values and each one of us strives everyday to be Champions for our customers, Challengers of convention and Cheerleaders for our team. Our renewed focus on improving the customer experience is making a big impact. We’ve seen overall customer complaints drop by 50%.2       



 Contact Information  If you are an investor or member of the news media, please contact the appropriate department listed below for more information about Nationstar Mortgage.   Shareholder Relations (972) 459-4904 Shareholders@nationstarmail.com   Media Relations (469) 549-3196 MediaRelations@nationstarmail.com     1Numbers reflect 12-month period ending September 2016 2Source: CFPB    
