Nationstar Mortgage Holdings In (NYSE:NSM) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsNationstar Mortgage Holdings In (NYSE:NSM) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume
July 25, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



(NYSE:NSM) shares saw light trading volume with 4,825 shares changing hands on Tuesday.  Overall, volume was down 99.54% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 These funds have also shifted positions in (NSM).   As of the end of the quarter Ranger Global Real Estate Advisors, LLC had disposed of 16,271 shares trimming its position 9.3%. The value of the total investment in Nationstar Mortgage Holdings In decreased from $3,153,000 to $2,832,000 a change of 10.2% for the reporting period. As of quarter end Nisa Investment Advisors, LLC had sold  a total of 800 shares trimming its holdings by 37.6%. The value of the investment in NSM went from $34,000 to $24,000 a change of $10,000 quarter to quarter.
 As of quarter end James Investment Research Inc had acquired  a total of 77,947 shares growing its stake by 72,173.1%. The value of the investment in (NSM) increased from $2,000 to $1,396,000 increasing 69,700.0% quarter over quarter. Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) reduced its investment by selling 1,205 shares a decrease of 89.6% from 12/31/2016 to 03/31/2017. Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) now controls 140 shares worth $2,000. The value of the position overall is down by 91.7%.
  On October 26, 2016 Nomura starting coverage on the stock by announcing an initial rating of “Buy”. On September 9 analysts at PiperJaffray initiated coverage on NSM with a rating of “Neutral” and establishing a price target of $15.50.        Advertisement






 On March 7 Credit Suisse maintained a stock rating of “Outperform” and lowered the price expectation  to $19.00 from $25.00. On December 16 the company was downgraded from “Equal-weight” to “Underweight” and a price target of $12.00 was set in a report issued by Morgan Stanley.
 Equity analyst Morgan Stanley downgraded the stock and lowered the price target  on December 16 cutting the price target from $19.00 to $12.00 and cutting the rating from “Equal-weight” to “Underweight”. November 4 investment analysts at Keefe Bruyette & Woods maintained a company rating of “Market Perform” but moved down the price target from $20.00 to $16.00.
 The company is so far trading up from yesterday’s close of $18.15.  Shares of the company are trading at $18.21 which is marginally higher than the 50 day moving average of $17.78 and marginally over the 200 day moving average of $17.35.  The 50 day moving average was up $0.43 or +2.41% and the 200 day average moved up $0.86. 
 The P/E ratio is currently 11.85 and the market cap of the company is 1.78B.  As of the latest earnings report the EPS was $1.54 and is projected to be $1.28 for the current year with 97,591,000 shares presently outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $0.43 with next year’s EPS projected to be $1.90. 
