Q:
Where can you learn how to make a solar system model for kids?


A:
Instructional outlets online such as How Stuff Works and About offer step-by-step instructions for creating several different types of solar system models. Premade model kits that require only minor assembly are also available through nearly all of the major online retailers .


See Full Answer

Filed Under:


K-12












Q:
Why do schools have summer vacation?


A:
Many people believe that the origins of summer vacation are rooted in America's agricultural past. However, it was actually the vacation habits of city kids and their families that inspired what is now considered the traditional American academic calendar. Wealthy families would take their children out of school during the hottest months in favor of vacationing in cooler locations.


See Full Answer

Filed Under:


K-12












Q:
What are some school bus safety tips?


A:
On the school bus, students should hold the handrail while entering and exiting, choose a seat, and sit down as quickly as possible. Passengers should talk quietly so that the driver is not distracted from driving safely and remain seated without extending their hands, arms or heads out of the windows. Bus riders should never throw things on the bus or out the windows.


See Full Answer

Filed Under:


K-12












Q:
Why should students read?


A:
Some of the reasons students should read include: vocabulary and fluency improvement, better comprehension skills and for fun. Reading skills carry many benefits for children of all ages.


See Full Answer

Filed Under:


K-12












Q:
Why are teachers important?


A:
Teachers are important because they not only provide instruction to children in one or more academic areas, depending on the grade level, but they also stand as an additional source of encouragement in the life of a child. Given the socioeconomic and family unit challenges that face so many students today, there are days when a child may only see a smile from his or her teacher, as all the other adults have so much stress going on that they are not able to convey love and acceptance.


See Full Answer

